The move will be seen as an attempt to counteract the success of Jeremy Corbyn's initiative to attract young voters with the promise of affordable housing and higher incomes.
The increase in the boiler tax will apply to individuals and companies that do not pay taxes in the UK, and the additional resources will support the Government's initiative to combat the phenomenon of homelessness.
